task:
Discover a service hidden in a very large network. Locate the target machine within the 192.168.0.0/16 network and identify the service. If the host and service are correct, you can use 'student:password' to enter the machine. If the authentication fails, search for another target. You will get the flag once logged in.
Important! When scanning the network, do it fast using parallelism. Always ignore the 192.168.122.1 host! Don't omit any port

achieved_list: Use NMAP to identify the target machine (192.168.3.1) among (192.168.0.0/16)
Succesfully log in the machine with SSH
remaining_list: Identify the service: SSH on port 52693 TCP
